ML-DSA stimulus.txt Format Reference
======================================

This document describes the format that stimulus.txt must contain for each
ML-DSA operation. The firmware reads stimulus.txt to obtain the test inputs.

All hex values are uppercase ASCII hex strings. Sizes shown are byte counts;
hex string lengths are bytes x 2.


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
keyGen (MLDSA_KEYGEN)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Lines: 2

    MLDSA_KEYGEN
    <seed>

Fields:
    seed   32 bytes (64 hex chars)   Random seed used to derive the key pair

Example:
    MLDSA_KEYGEN
    A1B2C3D4...  (64 hex chars)


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sigGen (MLDSA_SIGGEN)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Lines: 3 (without context) or 4 (with context)

    MLDSA_SIGGEN
    <sk>
    <msg>
    [<ctx>]

Fields:
    sk     4896 bytes (9792 hex chars)   ML-DSA-87 private (signing) key
    msg    variable                      Message to sign (hex)
    ctx    variable (optional)           Context string (hex); omitted if absent

Example (no context):
    MLDSA_SIGGEN
    A1B2C3D4...  (9792 hex chars)
    DEADBEEF...  (variable length)

Example (with context):
    MLDSA_SIGGEN
    A1B2C3D4...  (9792 hex chars)
    DEADBEEF...  (variable length)
    CAFEBABE...  (variable length)


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
sigVer (MLDSA_SIGVER)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Lines: 4 (without context) or 5 (with context)

    MLDSA_SIGVER
    <pk>
    <msg>
    <sig>
    [<ctx>]

Fields:
    pk     2592 bytes (5184 hex chars)   ML-DSA-87 public (verification) key
    msg    variable                      Message that was signed (hex)
    sig    4627 bytes (9254 hex chars)   Signature to verify
    ctx    variable (optional)           Context string (hex); omitted if absent

Example (no context):
    MLDSA_SIGVER
    A1B2C3D4...  (5184 hex chars)
    DEADBEEF...  (variable length)
    CAFEBABE...  (9254 hex chars)

Example (with context):
    MLDSA_SIGVER
    A1B2C3D4...  (5184 hex chars)
    DEADBEEF...  (variable length)
    CAFEBABE...  (9254 hex chars)
    01020304...  (variable length)


------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Firmware Output Format
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

After processing stimulus.txt, the firmware prints results to stdout.

    Operation    Output line
    ---------    -----------
    keyGen       MLDSA_PUBKEY:<pk_hex>
    keyGen       MLDSA_PRIVKEY:<sk_hex>
    sigGen       MLDSA_SIGGEN:<sig_hex>
    sigVer       MLDSA_SIGVER:<01 (pass) | 00 (fail)>
